OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNigeria's illegal oil      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Frefineries: Dirty,         
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdangerous, lucrative       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The deaths of more than 100 people     
OL,6, following an explosion at an illegal   
OL,7, oil refinery in southern Nigeria has   
OL,8, thrown a spotlight on the lucrative    
OL,9, world of illicit refining, which the   
OL,10, BBC's Mayeni Jones and Josephine       
OL,11, Casserly have been investigating.      
OL,13,FHours by car, motorbike and on foot    
OL,14,Fbrought us to a remote illegal oil     
OL,15,Frefinery - a site recently raided and  
OL,16,Fshut down by the authorities.          
OL,18,FThe smell of oil hits the nostrils     
OL,19,Ffirst before anything is visible. Then,
OL,20,Fthe lush green vegetation falls away   
OL,21,Fand we arrive at a blackened clearing. 
